Surrounded by nature on all sides, the Kruger Station brought its patrons something different this past weekend – the Kruger Station Gin Festival. This was the first of its kind, and the distillers and gin enthusiasts surely would not mind if this became a yearly gathering. ALSO READ: IN PHOTOS: White River Gallery exhibition shows visitors the life struggles of artists For just R125 per person, guests received a branded glass and the opportunity to taste some of the best gins available in South Africa. This included De Vry Distillery, Guardian Gin, Dollie Gin, Six Dogs, Old Packhouse Distillery, Ntwanano Gin, and Qualito Craft Distillery. ALSO READ: Bahati Centre, neighbours’ premises flooded in storm Tanya Cruse, a director/distiller of Gin & Co, said it was wonderful exposure for their Conservation Gin range. “It was nice to meet so many new people. Kruger Shalati is a wonderful venue and we hope it will become an annual event.”              Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram